Package swingtree.style

Class GradientStyle

  • java.lang.Object
    • swingtree.style.GradientStyle
  • public final class GradientStyle
extends java.lang.Object
    An immutable, wither-like copy method based config API for specifying a gradient style as a sub-style of various other styles, like for example BaseStyle or BorderStyle accessed through the ComponentStyleDelegate.gradient(String, Function) or ComponentStyleDelegate.borderGradient(String, Function) methods.

    The following properties with their respective purpose are available:

    • Transition

      The transition defines the direction of the gradient.
      The following transitions are available:
      • UI.Transition.TOP_LEFT_TO_BOTTOM_RIGHT
      • UI.Transition.BOTTOM_LEFT_TO_TOP_RIGHT
      • UI.Transition.TOP_RIGHT_TO_BOTTOM_LEFT
      • UI.Transition.BOTTOM_RIGHT_TO_TOP_LEFT
      • UI.Transition.TOP_TO_BOTTOM
      • UI.Transition.LEFT_TO_RIGHT
      • UI.Transition.BOTTOM_TO_TOP
      • UI.Transition.RIGHT_TO_LEFT

    • Type

      The type defines the shape of the gradient which can be either linear or radial.
      So the following types are available:
      • UI.GradientType.LINEAR
      • UI.GradientType.RADIAL

    • Colors

      An array of colors that will be used as a basis for the gradient transition.

    • Layer

      The layer defines if the gradient should be applied to the background or the border of a component.

    You can also use the none() method to specify that no gradient should be used, as the instance returned by that method is a gradient without any colors, effectively making it a representation of the absence of a gradient style.

      • colors

        public GradientStyle colors​(java.awt.Color... colors)
        Define a list of colors which will, as part of the gradient, transition from one to the next in the order they are specified.

        Note that you need to specify at least two colors for a gradient to be visible.

        Parameters:
        colors - The colors in the gradient.
        Returns:
        A new gradient style with the specified colors.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if any of the colors is null.
